{"favorite_id": 10191, "calc_type": "", "dosing": false, "full_title_en": "Kinetic Estimated Glomerular Filtration Rate (keGFR)", "short_title_en": "Kinetic Estimated Glomerular Filtration Rate (keGFR)", "medium_description_en": "Estimates GFR in patients with acutely changing creatinine.", "short_description_en": "keGFR estimation.", "before_use": "<p>This calculator includes inputs based on race, which may or may not provide better estimates, so we have decided to make race optional.&nbsp;<a target=\"_blank\" data-stringify-link=\"https://www.mdcalc.com/race\" delay=\"150\" data-sk=\"tooltip_parent\" href=\"https://www.mdcalc.com/race\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">See here</a>&nbsp;for more on our approach to addressing&nbsp;race and bias on MDCalc.</p>\n<p>For the same creatinine value, this calculator estimates a higher GFR for Black patients.</p>", "instructions_en": "<p>Take two serum creatinine measurements (Cr<sub>1</sub> and Cr<sub>2</sub>), at two different time points (time<sub>1</sub> and time<sub>2</sub>). Note: uses <calculator id=\"76\">MDRD</calculator> equation for calculating GFR.</p>", "purpose_en": ["Calculation"], "disease_en": ["Acute Kidney Injury", "Renal Failure"], "specialty_en": ["Hospitalist Medicine", "Internal Medicine", "Nephrology"], "chief_complaint_en": ["Anuria", "Shortness of Breath"], "system_en": ["Renal"], "search_abbreviation_en": ["Kgfr", "gfr", "Kinetic Glomerular Filtration Rate", "creatinine", "rrt", "renal replacement therapy", "aki", "kegfr"], "slug": "kinetic-estimated-glomerular-filtration-rate-kegfr", "seo": {"meta_description_en": "The Kinetic Glomerular Filtration Rate (kGFR) estimates GFR in patients with acutely changing creatinine.", "keywords_en": "Kgfr, gfr, Kinetic Glomerular Filtration Rate, creatinine, rrt, renal replacement therapy, aki, kegfr"}, "content": {"how_to_use": {"use_case_en": "", "pearls_pitfalls_en": "", "why_use_en": "<p>Other equations estimating GFR&nbsp;(<calculator id=\"43\">Cockcroft-Gault</calculator>, <calculator id=\"76\">MDRD</calculator>) have limited accuracy when creatinine is changing acutely.</p>"}, "next_steps": {"advice_en": "<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">While estimated GFR (by a validated equation) is adequate for most clinical scenarios, measured GFR is still considered the gold standard.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Remember, eGFR is an estimate of kidney function, but is not included in the definition of AKI.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>", "management_en": "", "critical_actions_en": ""}, "about": {"formula_en": "<p>Take two serum creatinine measurements (Cr<sub>1</sub> and Cr<sub>2</sub>), at two different time points (time<sub>1</sub> and time<sub>2</sub>).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"http://latex.codecogs.com/gif.latex?Kinetic%5C%20GFR%2C%20mL/min%20%3D%20%5Cfrac%7BCr_%7Bbaseline%7D%20%5Ctimes%20CrCl%7D%7BCr_%7Bmean%7D%7D%20%5Ctimes%20%5B1%20-%20%5Cfrac%7B24%20%5Ctimes%20%28Cr_2%20-%20Cr_1%29%7D%7B%28time_2%20-%20time_1%29%20%5Ctimes%201.5%7D%5D\" /></p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">where variables are as follows:</p>\n<div dir=\"ltr\">\n<table><colgroup><col width=\"92\" /><col width=\"357\" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Variable*</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Cr<sub>baseline </sub></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Baseline creatinine, mg/dL</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">CrCl</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Initial creatinine clearance, mL/min (by MDRD equation)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Cr<sub>mean</sub></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Average of Cr<sub>1</sub>&nbsp;and Cr<sub>2</sub></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">time<sub>2</sub> &ndash; time<sub>1</sub></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Time between measured Cr<sub>2</sub> and Cr<sub>1</sub>, hrs</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">*The second&nbsp;portion of the equation, i.e.,&nbsp;<em>1&nbsp;</em>&ndash;<em>&nbsp;[(24 x (Cr<sub>2</sub>&nbsp;</em>&ndash;<em>&nbsp;Cr<sub>1</sub>)) / ((time<sub>2</sub>&nbsp;</em>&ndash;<em>&nbsp;time<sub>1</sub>) x 1.5)]</em>,&nbsp;is a multiplier limited to 0-1.&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Note: formula assumes US units. For SI formula, see <a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28396736\" target=\"_blank\">O&rsquo;Sullivan 2017</a>.</p>", "more_info_en": "<p dir=\"ltr\">Interpretation:</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">KeGFR of 30 mL/min is 90% specific (71% sensitive) for AKI, according to one small retrospective study (<a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28396736\" target=\"_blank\">O'Sullivan 2017</a>).</p>", "evidence_based_medicine_en": "", "references_list": {"Original/Primary Reference": [{"href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23704286", "text": "Chen S. Retooling the creatinine clearance equation to estimate kinetic GFR when the plasma creatinine is changing acutely. J Am Soc Nephrol. 2013;24(6):877-88."}], "Other References": [], "Validation": [{"href": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/28396736", "text": "O'Sullivan ED, Doyle A. The clinical utility of kinetic glomerular filtration rate. Clin Kidney J. 2017;10(2):202-208."}], "Clinical Practice Guidelines": [], "Manufacturer Website": [], "Outcomes": []}}, "contributor": {"expert_name": []}, "creator": [{"name": "Dr. Sheldon Chen", "qa_en": "", "approved": false, "creator_info": {"about_en": "<p>Sheldon Chen, MD, is an associate professor in the department of nephrology at the MD Anderson Cancer Center in Houston, Texas. Previously, he was faculty at Northwestern University in Chicago, Illinois. Dr. Chen\u2019s primary research is focused on diabetic nephropathy and renal disease.</p>", "photo_en": "https://cdn-web-img.mdcalc.com/people/dr-sheldon-chen.jpg", "pubmedLink": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=Chen%20S%5BAuthor%5D&cauthor=true&cauthor_uid=23704286"}}], "reviewer": {"expert_name": []}, "related_resources": {"mdcalc_rating": [], "guidelines": [], "teaching": [], "videos": [], "interests": [], "partner_contact": [], "sdm_tool": []}}, "input_schema": [{"type": "toggle", "label_en": "Sex", "default": null, "conditionality": "", "show_points": false, "tips_en": "", "optional": false, "options": [{"label": "Female", "value": 1}, {"label": "Male", "value": 0}], "name": "sex"}, {"label_en": "Age", "conditionality": "", "default": null, "tips_en": "", "optional": false, "name": "age", "unit": "age", "type": "textbox", "unit_info": {"name": "Age", "conversion": 1, "error_min": 0.001, "error_max": 120, "warn_min": 0.1, "warn_max": 100, "normal_max_si": 0, "normal_min_si": 0, "normal_min_us": 0, "units_si": "years", "units_us": "years"}}, {"label_en": "Baseline creatinine", "conditionality": "", "default": null, "tips_en": "", "optional": false, "name": "Cr", "unit": "cr", "type": "textbox", "unit_info": {"name": "Creatinine", "conversion": 88.4, "error_min": 0.01, "error_max": 40, "warn_min": 0, "warn_max": 10, "normal_max_si": 115, "normal_min_si": 62, "normal_min_us": 0.7, "units_si": "\u00b5mol/L", "units_us": "mg/dL", "normal_max_us": 1.3}}, {"label_en": "First recorded creatinine (Cr<sub>1</sub>)", "conditionality": "", "default": null, "tips_en": "", "optional": false, "name": "Cr1", "unit": "cr", "type": "textbox", "unit_info": {"name": "Creatinine", "conversion": 88.4, "error_min": 0.01, "error_max": 40, "warn_min": 0, "warn_max": 10, "normal_max_si": 115, "normal_min_si": 62, "normal_min_us": 0.7, "units_si": "\u00b5mol/L", "units_us": "mg/dL", "normal_max_us": 1.3}}, {"label_en": "Second recorded creatinine (Cr<sub>2</sub>)", "conditionality": "", "default": null, "tips_en": "", "optional": false, "name": "Cr2", "unit": "cr", "type": "textbox", "unit_info": {"name": "Creatinine", "conversion": 88.4, "error_min": 0.01, "error_max": 40, "warn_min": 0, "warn_max": 10, "normal_max_si": 115, "normal_min_si": 62, "normal_min_us": 0.7, "units_si": "\u00b5mol/L", "units_us": "mg/dL", "normal_max_us": 1.3}}, {"label_en": "Time between both creatinine measurements", "conditionality": "", "default": null, "tips_en": "", "optional": false, "name": "t", "unit": "time", "type": "textbox", "unit_info": {"name": "Hours", "conversion": 1, "error_min": 0, "error_max": 72, "warn_min": 0.999, "warn_max": 24.001, "normal_max_si": 0, "normal_min_si": 0, "normal_min_us": 0, "units_si": "hours", "units_us": "hours"}}, {"type": "toggle", "label_en": "Black race", "default": null, "conditionality": "", "show_points": false, "tips_en": "Race may/may not provide better estimates of GFR; optional", "optional": true, "options": [{"label": "No", "value": 2}, {"label": "Yes", "value": 1}], "name": "race"}], "md5": "", "cmeReleaseDate": null, "cmeEndDate": null, "cmeLastReviewed": null, "related_calcs": [{"calcId": 76, "short_title_en": "MDRD GFR Equation", "slug": "mdrd-gfr-equation"}, {"calcId": 3939, "short_title_en": "CKD-EPI Equations for GFR", "slug": "ckdepi-equations-for-glomerular-filtration-rate-gfr"}, {"calcId": 43, "short_title_en": "Creatinine Clearance", "slug": "creatinine-clearance-cockcroft-gault-equation"}]}